This series is somewhat unique for Stratechery in that my interview subject=
s are generally not investors; this series, though, started in October 2022=
, when Friedman and Gross were launching a grant program, precisely because=
 we shared a sense that there wasn=E2=80=99t nearly enough activity or disc=
ussion around AI; one month later ChatGPT came out and the world has change=
d dramatically, including for Friedman and Gross, who are two of the leadin=
g investors in the space. To that end, I think it has been very valuable =
=E2=80=94 and popular =E2=80=94=C2=A0to continue this series, but do keep i=
n mind that Friedman and Gross may be invested in some of the companies we =
discuss.

That noted, this month has been particularly momentous in terms of AI news.=
 We try and cover all of it, from Gemini to Sora to Groq to Mistral to Nvid=
ia, as well as get into our usual philosophical questions about AI and what=
 might come next, particularly as companies attach different kinds of model=
s to transformers in the pursuit of reasoning.

As a reminder, all Stratechery content, including interviews, is available =
as a podcast; click the link at the top of this email to add Stratechery to=
 your podcast player.

