ige type of activity. It=E2=80=99s like benchmarks, right? But it has a hug=
e impact in the industry. When new benchmarks come out, people want to perf=
orm against those.

I think we have a bunch of challenges right now. First is that there are ve=
ry few good public evals and even the ones there are, like MMLU, they eithe=
r aren=E2=80=99t really able to predict certain types of capabilities or th=
ey=E2=80=99re getting close to saturated. I mean, on MMLU, you have people =
